    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-06T20:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-06T20:13:00-05:00" n="396"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2426</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-07T10:00:00+08:47">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3.18 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Your August 2, 6 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d396fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_323">p. 323</ref>.</note>
                    Impossible state strength of following of Siberian government without
                    information from western Siberia with which I have had no communication past
                    month. Either <pb facs="0423" n="333" xml:id="pg_333"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MDB1">Macgowan</persName> or <persName>Embry</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d396fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MDB1">David B. Macgowan</persName> and <persName>John
                            A. Embry</persName>, Consuls at Vladivostok.</note> willing to undertake
                    trip to [Omsk?] via Peking and Mongolian route in effort to secure such
                    information if Department considers expense and effort would be justified.
                    Hardly practicable. Instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJK1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
